com.commeto.kuleuven.MP.dataClasses

Class MeasurementArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.commeto.kuleuven.MP.dataClasses.MeasurementArray

  • public class MeasurementArray
extends java.lang.Object
     Created by Jonas on 1/03/2018.

 Class used to bundle all Measurements together with some additional ride info:
  - The name of the ride.
  - The start time of the ride.
  - The average speed.
  - The total distance.

      • toJson

        public int toJson(android.content.Context context,
                  java.lang.String username,
                  int calibration,
                  java.lang.String type)
           throws NoDistanceException
        Method to generate JSON representation of the MeasurementArray, writing it to storage and adding the info to the room database. Throw NoDistanceException if ride has no distance. Rides with no distance don't have to be saved.
        Parameters:
        context - Context of the application to use IO.
        username - Username of the rider.
        calibration - Used calibration.
        type - Type of the ride.
        Returns:
        Id generated for the route
        Throws:
        NoDistanceException - Thrown when ride has a distance of 0.
